body: I am not sure of this is a ONNX export issue. It is unlikely that the error message is coming from the ONNX exporter. Please take a look at the ONNX doc page and make sure that the export step is indeed happening correctly. If there are some input-dependent control flow (`if` and `loops`) in the model, then you will have to script that part of the model by putting scripting decorators (as shown on the page).

Hi  
According this article https://github.com/facebookresearch/detectron2/issues/629, "AliasWithName" is new export feature. 
Would some one please give me some ideas to deal with it? Thank you.

Hi
Form this article https://github.com/facebookresearch/detectron2/issues/872, If need to modify the onnx format, please also consider whether Caffe2 has a registration function or other functions that are not included in onnx. Please establish a mechanism. If special definitions are added to "Caffe2" in the future, it can also be processed synchronously with "onnx". Appreciate any help from the community!
@spandantiwari Sorry to bother you. Is there a solution to provide? thank you.
